    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="698"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d698">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 891.48/33</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Vice
                        Chairman of the American Red Cross</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WE1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 25, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: There is herewith enclosed to you a paraphrase of
                    a telegram dated January 22,<note n="2" xml:id="d698fn2">Text of telegram of
                        Jan. 22 printed <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note> from the American Minister at Teheran, relative to the famine conditions
                    in Persia.</p>
                <pb facs="0649" n="565" xml:id="pg_565"/>
                <p>Believing that a practical expression of American good will towards Persia, at
                    the present time, would be very beneficial, the Department feels that if the
                    American Red Cross is able to take any steps towards the alleviation of the
                    famine conditions in Persia, such action, under present conditions, would be
                    especially desirable.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
